import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import time



bool_cols = ['GridFins', 'Reused', 'Legs']
spaceX[bool_cols] = spaceX[bool_cols].astype(int)


category_features= ['BoosterVersion', 'Orbit', 'LandingPad', 'LaunchSite','Block']
spaceX = pd.get_dummies(spaceX, columns=category_features, drop_first=True)


drop_col = ['Date','Serial']
spaceX  = spaceX.drop(drop_col , axis=1)

fine tuning¶

In [110]:
def fine_tuning(model, param, param_values, X_train, y_train, cv=5):
    # Initialize variables to store the results
    mean_cv_scores = []

    # Loop through the parameter values
    for value in param_values:
        # Set the current parameter value
        model.set_params(**{param: value})

        # Compute cross-validated accuracy scores using the training data
        cv_scores = cross_val_score(model, X_train, y_train, cv=cv, scoring='accuracy')

        # Compute the mean cross-validated accuracy score
        mean_cv_score = np.mean(cv_scores)

        # Append the mean cross-validated score to the list
        mean_cv_scores.append(mean_cv_score)

    # Plot the mean cross-validated scores
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.plot(param_values, mean_cv_scores, marker='x')
    plt.xlabel(param)
    plt.ylabel("Mean Cross-Validated Accuracy")
    plt.title(model)
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()

from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix

y_pred = best_lr_classifier.predict(X_test)
cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
print(cm)
TN, FP, FN, TP = cm.ravel()
accuracy = (TP + TN) / (TP + TN + FP + FN)
precision = TP / (TP + FP)
recall = TP / (TP + FN)
f1 = 2 * (precision * recall) / (precision + recall)


print("Accuracy:", round(accuracy,3))
print("Precision:", round(precision,3))
print("Recall:", round(recall,3))
print("F1-score:", round(f1,3))

from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier

tree = DecisionTreeClassifier()


param_grid = {
    "criterion": ["gini", "entropy"],
    "max_depth": [4, 6, 10, 15],
    "min_samples_split": [2, 5, 10, 20],
    "min_samples_leaf": [1, 5, 10],
}


tree_grid_search = GridSearchCV(tree, param_grid, cv=5, scoring="accuracy")
tree_grid_search.fit(X_train, y_train)


best_params = tree_grid_search.best_params_
print("Best parameters:", best_params)

import pandas as pd


lr = {'Accuracy': 0.759, 'Precision': 0.867, 'Recall': 0.722, 'F1-score': 0.788}
dt = {'Accuracy': 0.862, 'Precision': 0.938, 'Recall': 0.833, 'F1-score': 0.882}
svm = {'Accuracy': 0.69, 'Precision': 0.8, 'Recall': 0.667, 'F1-score': 0.727}

# Combine the dictionaries 
data = {'Logistic Regression': lr, 'Decision Tree': dt, 'SVM': svm}

# Create a DataFrame from the dictionary
df = pd.DataFrame(data)

# Display the DataFrame
print(df)
